About the job
LEVEZ-VOUS POUR UNE BONNE RAISON !

Les 1500 collaborateurs du Groupe LGM, indépendant depuis sa création en 1991, travaillent chez nous parce qu'ils peuvent contribuer, aux côtés des principaux acteurs industriels des grands secteurs de l'industrie, à des projets complexes, passionnants, utiles, aujourd'hui ou demain.

LGM Belgium, filiale belge du groupe LGM, est à la recherche d’un ingénieur V&V F/H pour rejoindre ses équipes dynamiques et grandissantes basées à Charleroi.

POUR QUOI ?

S'assurer que les produits et équipements développés répondent aux normes et aux niveaux de conformité attendues.

COMMENT ?

En définissant et rédigeant des cas de test sur base de spécifications ;
En exécutant des tests et rédigeant des rapports ;
En analysant des erreurs et des bogues ;
En contribuant à l’enquête technique en cas de non-conformité de conception ;
En participant à l’analyse de la demande de changement ;
En contribuant aux revues et jalons de projets ;
En participant à l'élaboration/l’évolution des outils des tests et des processus en place ;
En assurant l’interface technique avec les clients internes/externes et les fournisseurs ;
En proposant des solutions techniques adaptées aux besoins de nos clients.

AVEC QUI/QUOI ?

Ingénieur V&V, justifiant d’une première expérience de minimum 3 ans, idéalement dans l'industrie du ferroviaire et/ou du spatial ;
Bonne connaissance des langages d'automatisation des tests comme Python ;
Bonne compréhension des schémas électroniques ;
Une rigueur et une volonté d'identifier les anomalies des systèmes ;
La capacité de comprendre les exigences des spécifications en utilisant une analyse critique ;
La capacité de suivre un processus interne défini ;
Un bon relationnel, qui vous permettra de vous adapter aux différents interlocuteurs ;
Une bonne maitrise de l’anglais technique.

About the job
LEVEZ-VOUS POUR UNE BONNE RAISON !

Les 800 collaborateurs de la société LGM, créée en 1991, travaillent chez nous parce qu'ils peuvent participer à l’amélioration de la performance de systèmes complexes, dans leur conception, production, exploitation et maintenance, en proposant des solutions (études et outils) en conseil et en formation.

De plus, si les grands systèmes vous fascinent et si travailler en collaboration avec d’autres services dans le développement et le design de ces systèmes vous intéresse ; alors le soutien logistique intégré vous permettra d’y répondre. Venez donc rejoindre nos équipes dynamiques et grandissantes de LGM Belgium, filiale du groupe LGM, en tant qu’ingénieur SLI (F/H) !

POUR QUOI ?

Rendre les systèmes et équipements plus durables, réutilisables, et mieux les employer en maitrisant leurs faiblesses et les moyens de les anticiper.

COMMENT ?

En analysant les besoins en maintenance des systèmes ;
En réalisant des analyses de maintenabilité telles que prévues dans les plans de management SLI et en accord avec les normes internationales en vigueur ainsi que la mise en œuvre des méthodes ASL (Analyse de Soutien Logistique) ;
En réalisant des études d’Analyse du Soutien Logistique (ASL) associé ;
En contribuant à l’établissement du plan de maintenance du système et à sa consolidation ;
En élaborant et en effectuant le maintien des bases de données logistiques ;
En influençant le développement ou l'exploitation du système et en permettant l’atteinte des objectifs de maintenabilité ;
En mesurant et en optimisant la cohérence et la performance du système de soutien ;
En consolidant un plan de maintenance préventif et correctif, c’est-à-dire de l’optimisation du temps des tâches et de l’harmonisation des intervalles de maintenance.

D’autres activités de l’ingénierie SLI vous seront également confiées, notamment des activités de documentation technique :

En identifiant des outillages spécifiques et rédigeant leurs spécifications ;
En rédigeant des fiches d’analyses, des plans et des manuels de maintenance ;
En rédigeant des manuels d’utilisation des produits / systèmes.

AVEC QUI/QUOI ?

Vous avez une expérience de deux ans en tant qu’ingénieur SLI ;
Les bureaux d'études, les équipementiers, les équipes logistiques et les utilisateurs finaux ;
Intégré(e) au sein d'une équipe LGM dynamique et pluridisciplinaire, qui n'a pas peur de relever les défis techniques ;
Un très bon relationnel pour animer des réunions et faire valoir les intérêts de la maintenance dans un environnement multi-métiers ;
Une capacité d'anticipation/projection, pour prévoir les problèmes ;
Une connaissance technique des systèmes et de la maintenance ;
Un esprit d'analyse pour comprendre les enjeux, les contraintes et les besoins client.

About the job
Bitdefender, a cybersecurity leader delivering best-in-class threat prevention, detection, and response solutions worldwide, is looking for a Full Stack Software Engineer to join our Threat Intelligence team.

Joining our team means building and maintaining a secure future for our Threat Intelligence customers in a fast evolving threat landscape by contributing to the development of our Advanced TI Portfolio. (https://www.bitdefender.com/oem/advanced-threat-intelligence.html)

We are looking for a person who is passionate about technology, methodical and pays very close attention to details, but who also has the initiative to challenge and improve existing routines and processes. All of the above with respect to the standards of quality, speed and stability Bitdefender proudly promotes.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop and maintain Threat Intelligence services with high availability & scalability requirements;
Active participation in each phase of development: design, develop, test, deploy, maintain and improve software;
Review requirements and propose architectures for scalability and reliability issues;
Analyze and evaluate technical requirements, the feasibility of ideas and proposed solutions;
Design and implement technical solutions that answer best client’s needs;
Ensure that the quality of the developed software permanently meets our high demands on quality by applying clean code practices;
Propose ideas of improvements of application, procedures and technologies used;
Support continuous improvement by investigating alternatives and staying up-to-date with modern technologies;
Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or a related field;
At least 3 years of experience in developing web applications;
Solid knowledge of design patterns and OOP principles;
Experience in exposing and integrating public APIs (REST);
Proficient understanding of web markup, including HTML5, CSS3 and experience writing cross-browser compatible code;
Experience in one or more relevant front-end frameworks (React, Angular, Vue.js, React.js, etc.);
The ability to switch between different technologies and stacks;
Have very good interpersonal and communication skills and love to be part of a team.
Any of the following it will be a plus:

Experience with Node.js;
Experience with NoSQL databases like MongoDB;
Experience with unit testing and testing frameworks (Jest, Mocha, Jasmine, Selenium, Karma, Protractor, etc.);
Benefits:

If you take up our offer, you will:

Be a member of a professional, motivated, and enthusiastic team;
Learn more about Cybersecurity and Threat Intelligence;
Work for a Romanian Company with worldwide presence and brand awareness;
Enjoy a remote-friendly culture and flexible work hours - results are more important than when the work is done;
Benefit from career development programs;
Enjoy a competitive salary, as well as private health insurance.

About the job
Trustpair is reinventing B2B payment security.

We are building the leading anti-fraud solution for large corporations to help them avoid $20 billion fraud every year.

With Trustpair, finance teams work with accurate data to avoid the risk of fraud and proceed to payments with peace of mind.

Trustpair is the best-in-breed product against B2B payment fraud and it must stay this way!

Today a market-leader, Trustpair aggregates more data sources than its competitors, leverages on a bigger amount of payment data, making an intelligent use of the data collected.

We are opening a position for an SRE to join our growing Engineering team!

With a strong focus on our production environments, you will apply your expertise to operating and managing our cloud-based applications and ensure that our clients and partners can rely on us for their day-to-day financial operations.

As the first dedicated Site Reliability Engineer and with the help of the team, you will need to ensure our services run stable, have high availability, and are cost-effective.

You will help your peers set up efficient observability and fix production problems to ensure minimal impact on our business.

You can make decisions regarding product infrastructure architecture and refine our GitLab CI/CD pipelines to maximize velocity and consistency.

Your role:

Our production and development stack is using a hybrid infrastructure, based on scalable private runtimes on Heroku and services on the AWS cloud. The observability of this architecture is handled by New Relic.

By joining the team, your two first main focus will be to ensure:

Scalability for the long run

Leverage an AWS-driven infrastructure using the latest DevOps and Infrastructure as Code frameworks and best practices;
Design and implement system automation architecture, infrastructure, and process;
Focus on performance, and scalability, as well as resource optimization;
Ensure systems are secure and compliant with industry best practices

Reliability for our clients

Ensure the availability of our services, build the tools and automation to monitor and enable this availability;
Perform quick and accurate troubleshooting, and diagnostic of the production system;
Build monitoring that alerts on symptoms rather than on outages

Over time, you could also expand your scope to work with the team on internal solutions and engineering experience.

Implement solutions to optimize developer velocity and experience;
Refine, improve and enhance our CI/CD;
Manage development, staging and sandboxes environments for a smooth Developer Experience

Why join Trustpair - list of our perks here !

MUST HAVE

4+ years experience in a System Engineering / DevOps / SRE position;
Strong experience in SaaS solution deployment; migrating, architecting, building, and deploying systems and applications to a public Cloud;
Experience in high-scalability architecture;
Know your way around Linux and the Unix Shell;
Hands on experience in AWS cloud services;
Experience with infrastructure as code (Terraform, CloudFormation);
Experience in infrastructure monitoring solution deployment (New Relic or equivalent);
Fluent in English;
Strong problem solving, analytical and troubleshooting skills;
Autonomous and adaptable, organizational skills

Recruitment Process

Call with Aicha, Talent Partner (30 min);
Call with our CTO and co-founder, Simon (1h30);
Case study (should take around 2 hours of work on a 1 week timeframe) - 1h30 restitution;
Test restitution and Coffee Fit with Principal Engineer, Michaël + Data Engineer, Alexandre (1h30);
Culture fit with the team (45 min)

SALARY RANGE FOR THIS POSITION: €58-68k / year for FTE or €500 / day for B2B contract

Equal Opportunity Statement

Trustpair's policy is to provide equal employment opportunity in all of our employment practices without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, ancestry, marital status, protected veteran status, age, individuals with disabilities, sexual orientation or gender identity or expression or any other legally protected category.

Applicants for all positions in Trustpair must be legally authorized to work in the country which they are applying for or be a citizen from Schengen / EU zone. The verification of employment eligibility will be required as a condition of hire.

About the job
Description

Our partner delivers fast, reliable solutions for connectivity, trading and compliance. Customers rely on their solutions to consolidate their connectivity and trading infrastructure, addressing the full trade lifecycle across asset classes.

Their offering reflects our unique design philosophy. A modular architecture with open interfaces to facilitate business-specific deployment as well as integration with third parties. For their customers, this flexibility translates into agility, meaning faster time-to-market and the ability to quickly adapt to business needs and regulatory change.

Role Overview

Our partner is seeking software engineering talent to help them drive their strategic vision of transforming the trading landscape for their clients globally.

They are looking for talented, self-motivated individuals with a desire to learn, build deep expertise, and create impact working collaboratively. Their associates embrace change, easily integrate and succeed in a global fast-paced environment. If you believe you have what they are looking for, they invite you to be part of their global network of talented, client-focused, forward-thinking teams where your contributions will be recognized and rewarded helping you to progress your career.

